  "claim_short": "The real-line question in Remark 4.4 has an affirmative answer. Let f:R -> R be Lipschitz and topologically transitive, and suppose that f has a fixed point. Point R at such a fixed point, so that the Lipschitz-free linearization widehat f is defined on F(R). Then widehat f is weakly mixing, hence hypercyclic. Moreover widehat f has dense periodic points, so it is Devaney chaotic.",
